b"Repost from @WaltDisneyImagineering:

Concept artist Nikkolas Smith was among the first to see his artwork, \xe2\x80\x9cKing Chad,\xe2\x80\x9d displayed in Downtown Disney. The art installation pays tribute to Black Panther star Chadwick Boseman with the inscription: 

\xe2\x80\x9cAs a former Disney Imagineer, I had the honor of working on a major children's hospital initiative and Avengers Campus as my final two assignments. Seeing Chadwick's heart for people in-person, and later discovering his courageous battle with cancer, I was inspired to create this tribute to honor his life and legacy. To us, he was and will always be T'Challa. Long Live The King.\xe2\x80\x9d"
